{{LaoText}}
The '''Lao Loum''' ({{lang-lo|ລາວລຸ່ມ}}; {{lang-th|ลาวลุ่ม}}, {{RTGS|''Lao Lum''}}, {{IPA-th|lāːw lûm|pron}}) is an official [[Laos|Lao People's Democratic Republic]] designation for lowland dwelling Tai peoples, including the majority [[Lao people]]. The Lao Loum, literally meaning "lowland Lao," are the inhabitants of the river valleys and lowlands along the [[Mekong River]] and make up over 68% of the population of Laos, of whom, half are of the Lao ethnic group. Other members categorised as Lao Loum are the other large Tai groups, such as the [[Phuan people|Phuan]] and [[Phuthai]] and other closely related members of Tai ethnic groups.
