{{for|the language|Shiriana language}}
The '''Shiriana''' (sometimes called the '''Xiriâna''') are a [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] tribe of [[Brazil]] with a current population of approximately 1,000.  They speak the [[Shiriana language]], and are primarily [[animism|animists]].  Most live in the Brazilian state of [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], but there are small groups living as well in [[Venezuela]], near the [[Demeni]] and the [[Rio Negro (Amazon)|Rio Negro]].

