'''''The Gold Bar Reporter''''' is an online activist community website based around [[Gold Bar, Washington|Gold Bar]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]].

==History==
''The Gold Bar Reporter'' was first published in 2006.

Its founder, Ann Block, is a former lawyer who was disbarred by the Washington State Bar Association in 2016. Since her disbarment, Ms. Block has used the Gold Bar Reporter to voice her personal grievances against the Washington State Bar Association and local lawyers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.heraldnet.com/news/state-supreme-court-disbars-gold-bar-lawyer/|title=State Supreme Court disbars Gold Bar lawyer {{!}} HeraldNet.com|date=2016-07-16|work=HeraldNet.com|access-date=2018-08-20|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/activists-website-hammers-away-at-gold-bar-costs-tiny-town-money/|title=Activist’s website hammers away at Gold Bar, costs tiny town money|date=2012-02-09|work=The Seattle Times|access-date=2018-08-20|language=en-US}}</ref>

